rComments: Get a chat in with her. She was very reasonable, but you are expected to communicate. She has her opinions and she allows you to have yours. Takes a balanced approach. She likes her group reading circles, so be prepared to collaborate with your peers.

Dr Ausman is an awesome professor, very caring, fair grader, accessible outside class time, gives excellent feedback, clear directions, works closely with students through their projects, goes above and beyond to help them and on top she is hilarious. I would blindly recommend her for any course she is teaching
Okay, but seems to emphasize creativity too much. If your assignments are not "off the wall" enough, you won't do that well.
